HEADWORD: Disjunction
<hw>Dis*junc"tion</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>disjunctio</ets>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>The act of disjoining;
disunion; separation; a parting; <as>as, the <ex>disjunction</ex> of
soul and body</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>A disjunctive proposition.</def>
<rj><au>Coleridge.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Disjunctive</ent>⟦br⟧
